4348/**
4349 * __vmw_execbuf_release_pinned_bo - Flush queries and unpin the pinned
4350 * query bo.
4351 *
4352 * @dev_priv: The device private structure.
4353 * @fence: If non-NULL should point to a struct vmw_fence_obj issued
4354 * _after_ a query barrier that flushes all queries touching the current
4355 * buffer pointed to by @dev_priv->pinned_bo
4356 *
4357 * This function should be used to unpin the pinned query bo, or
4358 * as a query barrier when we need to make sure that all queries have
4359 * finished before the next fifo command. (For example on hardware
4360 * context destructions where the hardware may otherwise leak unfinished
4361 * queries).
4362 *
4363 * This function does not return any failure codes, but make attempts
4364 * to do safe unpinning in case of errors.
4365 *
4366 * The function will synchronize on the previous query barrier, and will
4367 * thus not finish until that barrier has executed.
4368 *
4369 * the @dev_priv->cmdbuf_mutex needs to be held by the current thread
4370 * before calling this function.
4371 */
4372void __vmw_execbuf_release_pinned_bo(struct vmw_private *dev_priv,
4373 struct vmw_fence_obj *fence)
4374{
4375 int ret = 0;
4376 struct list_head validate_list;
4377 struct ttm_validate_buffer pinned_val, query_val;
4378 struct vmw_fence_obj *lfence = NULL;
4379 struct ww_acquire_ctx ticket;
4380
4381 if (dev_priv->pinned_bo == NULL)
4382 goto out_unlock;
4383
4384 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&validate_list);
4385
4386 pinned_val.bo = ttm_bo_reference(&dev_priv->pinned_bo->base);
4387 pinned_val.shared = false;
4388 list_add_tail(&pinned_val.head, &validate_list);
4389
4390 query_val.bo = ttm_bo_reference(&dev_priv->dummy_query_bo->base);
4391 query_val.shared = false;
4392 list_add_tail(&query_val.head, &validate_list);
4393
4394 ret = ttm_eu_reserve_buffers(&ticket, &validate_list,
4395 false, NULL);
4396 if (unlikely(ret != 0)) {
4397 vmw_execbuf_unpin_panic(dev_priv);
4398 goto out_no_reserve;
4399 }
4400
4401 if (dev_priv->query_cid_valid) {
4402 BUG_ON(fence != NULL);
4403 ret = vmw_fifo_emit_dummy_query(dev_priv, dev_priv->query_cid);
4404 if (unlikely(ret != 0)) {
4405 vmw_execbuf_unpin_panic(dev_priv);
4406 goto out_no_emit;
4407 }
4408 dev_priv->query_cid_valid = false;
4409 }
4410
4411 vmw_bo_pin_reserved(dev_priv->pinned_bo, false);
4412 if (dev_priv->dummy_query_bo_pinned) {
4413 vmw_bo_pin_reserved(dev_priv->dummy_query_bo, false);
4414 dev_priv->dummy_query_bo_pinned = false;
4415 }
4416 if (fence == NULL) {
4417 (void) vmw_execbuf_fence_commands(NULL, dev_priv, &lfence,
4418 NULL);
4419 fence = lfence;
4420 }
4421 ttm_eu_fence_buffer_objects(&ticket, &validate_list, (void *) fence);
4422 if (lfence != NULL)
4423 vmw_fence_obj_unreference(&lfence);
4424
4425 ttm_bo_unref(&query_val.bo);
4426 ttm_bo_unref(&pinned_val.bo);
4427 vmw_dmabuf_unreference(&dev_priv->pinned_bo);
4428out_unlock:
4429 return;
4430
4431out_no_emit:
4432 ttm_eu_backoff_reservation(&ticket, &validate_list);
4433out_no_reserve:
4434 ttm_bo_unref(&query_val.bo);
4435 ttm_bo_unref(&pinned_val.bo);
4436 vmw_dmabuf_unreference(&dev_priv->pinned_bo);
4437}

4439/**
4440 * vmw_execbuf_release_pinned_bo - Flush queries and unpin the pinned
4441 * query bo.
4442 *
4443 * @dev_priv: The device private structure.
4444 *
4445 * This function should be used to unpin the pinned query bo, or
4446 * as a query barrier when we need to make sure that all queries have
4447 * finished before the next fifo command. (For example on hardware
4448 * context destructions where the hardware may otherwise leak unfinished
4449 * queries).
4450 *
4451 * This function does not return any failure codes, but make attempts
4452 * to do safe unpinning in case of errors.
4453 *
4454 * The function will synchronize on the previous query barrier, and will
4455 * thus not finish until that barrier has executed.
4456 */
4457void vmw_execbuf_release_pinned_bo(struct vmw_private *dev_priv)
4458{
4459 mutex_lock(&dev_priv->cmdbuf_mutex);
4460 if (dev_priv->query_cid_valid)
4461 __vmw_execbuf_release_pinned_bo(dev_priv, NULL);
4462 mutex_unlock(&dev_priv->cmdbuf_mutex);
4463}
4464
4465int vmw_execbuf_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, unsigned long data,
4466 struct drm_file *file_priv, size_t size)
4467{
4468 struct vmw_private *dev_priv = vmw_priv(dev);
4469 struct drm_vmw_execbuf_arg arg;
4470 int ret;
4471 static const size_t copy_offset[] = {
4472 offsetof(struct drm_vmw_execbuf_arg, context_handle),
4473 sizeof(struct drm_vmw_execbuf_arg)};
4474 struct dma_fence *in_fence = NULL;
4475
4476 if (unlikely(size < copy_offset[0])) {
4477 DRM_ERROR("Invalid command size, ioctl %d\n",
4478 DRM_VMW_EXECBUF);
4479 return -EINVAL;
4480 }
4481
4482 if (copy_from_user(&arg, (void __user *) data, copy_offset[0]) != 0)
4483 return -EFAULT;
4484
4485 /*
4486 * Extend the ioctl argument while
4487 * maintaining backwards compatibility:
4488 * We take different code paths depending on the value of
4489 * arg.version.
4490 */
4491
4492 if (unlikely(arg.version > DRM_VMW_EXECBUF_VERSION ||
4493 arg.version == 0)) {
4494 DRM_ERROR("Incorrect execbuf version.\n");
4495 return -EINVAL;
4496 }
4497
4498 if (arg.version > 1 &&
4499 copy_from_user(&arg.context_handle,
4500 (void __user *) (data + copy_offset[0]),
4501 copy_offset[arg.version - 1] -
4502 copy_offset[0]) != 0)
4503 return -EFAULT;
4504
4505 switch (arg.version) {
4506 case 1:
4507 arg.context_handle = (uint32_t) -1;
4508 break;
4509 case 2:
4510 default:
4511 break;
4512 }
4513
4514
4515 /* If imported a fence FD from elsewhere, then wait on it */
4516 if (arg.flags & DRM_VMW_EXECBUF_FLAG_IMPORT_FENCE_FD) {
4517 in_fence = sync_file_get_fence(arg.imported_fence_fd);
4518
4519 if (!in_fence) {
4520 DRM_ERROR("Cannot get imported fence\n");
4521 return -EINVAL;
4522 }
4523
4524 ret = vmw_wait_dma_fence(dev_priv->fman, in_fence);
4525 if (ret)
4526 goto out;
4527 }
4528
4529 ret = ttm_read_lock(&dev_priv->reservation_sem, true);
4530 if (unlikely(ret != 0))
4531 return ret;
4532
4533 ret = vmw_execbuf_process(file_priv, dev_priv,
4534 (void __user *)(unsigned long)arg.commands,
4535 NULL, arg.command_size, arg.throttle_us,
4536 arg.context_handle,
4537 (void __user *)(unsigned long)arg.fence_rep,
4538 NULL,
4539 arg.flags);
4540 ttm_read_unlock(&dev_priv->reservation_sem);
4541 if (unlikely(ret != 0))
4542 goto out;
4543
4544 vmw_kms_cursor_post_execbuf(dev_priv);
4545
4546out:
4547 if (in_fence)
4548 dma_fence_put(in_fence);
4549 return ret;
4550}
